name: Spaghetti Carbonara
steps: Boil spaghetti in salted water until al dente.
Whisk eggs and parmesan cheese together in a bowl.
Cook pancetta in a skillet until crispy.
Drain spaghetti and mix with pancetta in the skillet.
Remove from heat and stir in the egg and cheese mixture.
Season with black pepper and serve immediately.

name: Chicken Adobo
steps: Marinate chicken with soy sauce and crushed garlic for 30 minutes.
Place marinated chicken in a pot and add vinegar, bay leaves, peppercorns, and sugar.
Simmer over medium heat until chicken is tender and sauce thickens.
Serve with steamed rice.

name: Sushi Rolls
steps: Cook sushi rice according to package instructions and let cool.
Place a nori sheet shiny side down on a bamboo mat.
Spread a thin layer of rice over the nori.
Add fish, avocado, and cucumber as fillings.
Roll tightly using the bamboo mat and slice into bite-sized pieces.
Serve with soy sauce and wasabi.

name: Tacos
steps: Cook ground beef in a skillet with taco seasoning.
Warm tortillas in a pan or microwave.
Fill tortillas with cooked beef, chopped onion, diced tomato, shredded lettuce, and cheese.
Serve with salsa or sour cream, if desired.

name: Pancakes
steps: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a bowl.
Whisk milk, egg, and melted butter together.
Combine wet and dry ingredients to form a smooth batter.
Pour batter into a hot, buttered skillet and cook until bubbles form on the surface.
Flip and cook until golden brown on the other side.
Serve with syrup or your favorite toppings.

name: Bibimbap
steps: Cook rice and set aside.
SautÃ© spinach, carrot, and zucchini in sesame oil.
Cook beef slices in soy sauce and garlic.
Assemble rice, vegetables, and beef in a bowl.
Top with a fried egg and a dollop of gochujang.

name: Tom Yum Soup
steps: Bring chicken stock to a boil with lemongrass, galangal, and lime leaves.
Add mushrooms and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.
Season with fish sauce and chili paste.
Serve with a squeeze of lime.

name: Butter Chicken
steps: Marinate chicken with spices and yogurt.
Cook chicken in butter until browned.
Prepare a sauce with tomatoes, cream, onion, and garlic.
Simmer chicken in the sauce for 20 minutes.
Serve with naan or rice.

name: Greek Salad
steps: Chop tomatoes, cucumber, and red onion.
Combine vegetables in a bowl with feta and olives.
Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with oregano.
Serve immediately.

name: Beef Stroganoff
steps: SautÃ© beef strips in butter until browned.
Cook mushrooms and onions in the same pan.
Prepare a sauce with butter, flour, and beef broth.
Mix in sour cream and simmer with beef.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

name: Pad Thai
steps: Soak rice noodles in water until soft.
Cook shrimp in a hot wok.
Add beaten egg and scramble.
Mix in tamarind paste, fish sauce, and noodles.
Toss with bean sprouts and crushed peanuts.

name: Sinigang
steps: Boil pork pieces in water with tomatoes and onions
Add tamarind base or fresh tamarind and simmer until meat is tender
Add vegetables starting with the firmest (eggplant, string beans)
Add leafy vegetables (kangkong) last
Season with fish sauce and serve hot

name: Pancit Bihon
steps: Soak rice noodles in warm water
Stir-fry chicken pieces until cooked
Add vegetables and cook until tender-crisp
Add drained noodles and season with soy sauce
Garnish with green onions and serve with calamansi

name: Kare Kare
steps: Cook oxtail in pressure cooker until tender
Make sauce with peanut butter and ground toasted rice
Add vegetables in stages based on cooking time
Simmer until sauce thickens
Serve with shrimp paste on the side

name: Mac and Cheese
steps: Cook macaroni according to package directions
Make roux with butter and flour, add milk to make bechamel
Stir in cheese and seasonings until melted
Mix sauce with cooked pasta
Top with breadcrumbs and bake until bubbly

name: Sisig
steps: Boil pork face until tender, then grill until crispy
Chop grilled pork into small pieces
Mix with chopped chicken liver and onions
Season with calamansi juice and chili
Serve on sizzling plate topped with egg

name: Lasagna
steps: Make meat sauce with ground beef and tomatoes
Mix ricotta with eggs and parmesan
Layer noodles, meat sauce, and cheese mixture
Top with mozzarella
Bake covered, then uncovered until golden

name: Chicken Tinola
steps: SautÃ© ginger, garlic, and onion
Add chicken pieces and cook until lightly browned
Pour in water and simmer until chicken is tender
Add green papaya chunks
Add chili leaves and season with fish sauce

name: Shepherd's Pie
steps: Cook ground lamb with vegetables and gravy
Make mashed potatoes with butter and milk
Layer meat mixture in baking dish
Top with mashed potatoes and create peaks
Bake until golden brown on top

name: Bicol Express
steps: SautÃ© garlic, ginger, and onion
Add pork and cook until lightly browned
Add shrimp paste and chili peppers
Pour in coconut milk and simmer until thick
Adjust spiciness to taste

name: Chicken Pot Pie
steps: Cook chicken and vegetables in butter
Make cream sauce with flour and chicken broth
Combine sauce with chicken and vegetables
Pour into pie crust-lined dish
Top with second crust and bake until golden
